Sentencas: A well-connected and high-porosity current collector layer fabricated at a low temperature of 550 degrees C is designed for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 (MCO) powders are used as the binder through the reforming of MCO in the air atmosphere.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A high conductivity phase La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) is added to keep the porous frame microstructure and decease the ohmic polarization of the current collector layer.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three current collector layers are prepared: MCO, MCO/LSCF, and LSCF.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The working state of each current collector layer in planar SOFC stack is reproduced by special experimental design; the performance is tested in the range of 550-750 degrees C.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the current collector layer for SOFC is achieved at low temperatures using the reduction-oxidation properties of MCO, and the performance is improved by adding high conductivity phase LSCF.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The gas distribution at the cathode side is also simulated for designing a high performance SOFC.
Titulo: High performance of ceramic current collector fabricated at 550 °C through in-situ joining of reduced Mn1.5Co1.5O4 for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
